05/06/2003
BIJELJINA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Police in Bijeljina arrested five arms smugglers Tuesday (3 June).
The operation took place in the eastern BiH area of Vlasenica.
The police seized 11 automatic rifles and large quantities of ammunition.
The smugglers were planning to sell the weapons.
Also Tuesday, SFOR searched for weapons in 18 homes in Bosanska Jagodina and Pijavica.
The SRNA news agency quoted sources as saying the operation was partially successful in finding arms.
In Visegrad, SFOR and local authorities are running the Harvest operation for collection of illegally possessed weapons until 22 June.
(SRNA, Onasa - 04/06/03)
